The R33 between Dundee and Pomeroy in KZN is still closed after angry residents blockaded the road with stones and debris on Wednesday morning. A group of more than 80 protesters gathered on the R33 and burnt tyres. Sources in the area told The Witness that the protesters are demanding that uMzinyathi District Municipality provide them with clean water. Ward councillor Xolani Mkhize said, “We have had numerous meetings with the residents to give them an update on a water project that is still in the pipeline. We will be meeting with them again today to introduce the contractor,” he said. KZN police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Nqobile Gwala said, “The road is still closed. No case was opened and no damages were reported. Helpmekaar SAPS are monitoring the situation.”